# Part 5 — Auth & Onboarding + Frontend Architecture

---

## 6. Authentication & Onboarding Flow

### 6.1 Supabase Auth Setup

**Auth methods**: Email/password (primary), magic link (secondary).

Supabase project config:
- Enable email auth in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers
- Disable email confirmation for MVP (reduces friction for African markets where email verification rates are low) — enable in Phase 2
- Set redirect URLs: `http://localhost:3000`, `https://yourdomain.com`

**Supabase client setup:**

```typescript
// src/lib/supabase/client.ts — Browser client
import { createBrowserClient } from '@supabase/ssr';

export function createClient() {
  return createBrowserClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
  );
}
```

```typescript
// src/lib/supabase/server.ts — Server client (App Router)
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';

export async function createServerSupabase() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  return createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll() { return cookieStore.getAll(); },
        setAll(cookiesToSet) {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) => {
            cookieStore.set(name, value, options);
          });
        },
      },
    }
  );
}
```

```typescript
// src/lib/supabase/admin.ts — Service role (server-only, bypasses RLS)
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

export function createServiceRoleClient() {
  return createClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY!
  );
}
```

### 6.2 Middleware Route Protection

```typescript
// src/middleware.ts
import { NextResponse, type NextRequest } from 'next/server';
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';

const publicPaths = [
  '/', '/signin', '/signup', '/forgot-password', '/reset-password',
  '/pricing', '/terms', '/privacy',
];

const authPaths = ['/signin', '/signup', '/forgot-password', '/reset-password'];

export async function middleware(req: NextRequest) {
  const res = NextResponse.next();

  const supabase = createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll() { return req.cookies.getAll(); },
        setAll(cookiesToSet) {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) => {
            req.cookies.set(name, value);
            res.cookies.set(name, value, options);
          });
        },
      },
    }
  );

  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
  const path = req.nextUrl.pathname;
  const isPublic = publicPaths.some(p => path === p) || path.startsWith('/invite');

  // Not logged in → redirect to signin (unless public path)
  if (!user && !isPublic) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/signin', req.url));
  }

  // Logged in → redirect away from auth pages
  if (user && authPaths.some(p => path === p)) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/app/chat', req.url));
  }

  // Logged in + accessing /app/* → check if onboarded
  if (user && path.startsWith('/app')) {
    const { data: member } = await supabase
      .from('business_members')
      .select('business_id')
      .eq('user_id', user.id)
      .limit(1)
      .single();

    if (!member) {
      // No business → redirect to onboarding
      return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/onboarding', req.url));
    }
  }

  return res;
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|icons|manifest.json).*)'],
};
```

### 6.3 Session Management

- Sessions are managed via Supabase's `sb-*` cookies set by `@supabase/ssr`
- Sessions persist across tabs (same cookie)
- Session refresh: Supabase auto-refreshes JWT tokens before expiry
- Logout: call `supabase.auth.signOut()` → clears cookies → redirect to `/signin`
- Cross-tab sync: use `supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange()` listener in a `useEffect` in the root layout to detect logout in other tabs

### 6.4 Onboarding Wizard

**3 steps, each its own component:**

**Step 1 — Business Info:**
- Fields: Business name (required), Business type (select: retail, pharmacy, restaurant, wholesale, beauty, other)
- Validation: Zod schema `{ name: z.string().min(2).max(100), type: z.enum([...]) }`

**Step 2 — Currency & Location:**
- Fields: Currency (select: NGN, GHS, KES, ZAR, USD, GBP), Default location name (text, e.g., "Main Store"), Address (optional)
- Validation: `{ currency: z.string().length(3), locationName: z.string().min(2) }`

**Step 3 — Guided First Chat:**
- Shows a mock chat interface with a pre-written suggestion: "I just bought 50 boxes of paracetamol for ₦200 each"
- User taps Send → real API call → AI parses → confirmation card appears → user taps Confirm → transaction created
- On confirm success, redirect to `/app/chat` with a "Welcome to Stoka!" toast

**What gets created on completion:**

| Step | DB Write |
|------|----------|
| Step 1 submit | `businesses` row + `business_members` row (role: owner) |
| Step 2 submit | `locations` row (is_default: true) |
| Step 3 confirm | `transactions` row + `transaction_items` + `stock_levels` + `products` + `product_variants` (if new) |

### 6.5 Invitation Flow

1. Owner navigates to Settings → Team → clicks "Invite Member"
2. Enters: email, role (manager or staff)
3. POST `/api/invitations` → creates `invitations` row with unique token, expires in 7 days
4. Email sent via Supabase's built-in email (or Resend as an alternative) with link: `https://stoka.app/invite/{token}`
5. Recipient clicks link → `/invite/[token]` page:
   - If authenticated: POST `/api/invitations/accept` → validates token → checks expiry → creates `business_members` row → marks invitation as accepted → redirect to `/app/chat`
   - If not authenticated: page shows "Create an account to join [Business Name]" → links to `/signup?invite={token}` → after signup, the `invite` query param triggers auto-acceptance

---

## 7. Frontend Architecture Plan

### 7.1 Component Hierarchy

```
src/
├── app/                          # Next.js App Router
│   ├── (auth)/                   # Auth route group (no app shell)
│   ├── (app)/                    # App route group (with app shell)
│   │   ├── layout.tsx            # Fetches user/business, provides context
│   │   ├── app/
│   │   │   ├── chat/
│   │   │   ├── dashboard/
│   │   │   ├── products/
│   │   │   ├── inventory/
│   │   │   ├── transactions/
│   │   │   ├── suppliers/
│   │   │   ├── customers/
│   │   │   ├── insights/
│   │   │   └── settings/
│   │   └── onboarding/
│   └── (public)/                 # Landing + public pages (no app shell)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                       # Atomic components (Button, Input, Badge, Card, etc.)
│   ├── auth/                     # AuthForm, RoleGate
│   ├── layout/                   # AppShell, Sidebar, MobileNav, ContextPanel
│   ├── chat/                     # ChatContainer, ChatMessage, ChatInput, ConfirmationCard
│   ├── dashboard/                # KPICard, charts, tables
│   ├── products/                 # ProductTable, ProductForm, VariantForm
│   ├── inventory/                # StockTable, LowStockAlert
│   ├── transactions/             # TransactionTable, TransactionDetail, StatusBadge
│   ├── contacts/                 # ContactTable, ContactForm (shared suppliers/customers)
│   ├── insights/                 # InsightCard, InsightList
│   ├── settings/                 # SettingsLayout, BusinessForm, TeamTable
│   ├── onboarding/               # Wizard steps
│   ├── landing/                  # Hero, Features, Pricing, etc.
│   └── pwa/                      # InstallPrompt
├── stores/                       # Zustand stores
├── lib/                          # Utilities, hooks, AI, Supabase
└── types/                        # TypeScript types
```

**Reusability principles:**
- `ui/` components are style-only, no business logic
- `ContactTable` and `ContactForm` are shared between suppliers and customers (parameterized by entity type)
- `ProductForm` is reused for create and edit (pre-filled for edit)
- `StatusBadge` is reused across transactions, insights, and inventory

